articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel's centrist war cabinet minister Benny Gantz is scheduled to give a speech later on Saturday in which he is widely expected to announce his resignation from Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's emergency government.
articles.title: Israel's war cabinet minister Gantz expected to quit Netanyahu government

articles.author: Jeff Mason, Michel Rose
articles.description: Fresh from commemorating the 80th anniversary of D-Day, French President Emmanuel Macron will host U.S. President Joe Biden on Saturday for a state visit marked by pomp and a parade as well as talks on trade, Israel and Ukraine.
articles.title: Biden, Macron to discuss Israel and Ukraine in pomp-filled state visit

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Humanitarian aid entering Gaza by sea via a U.S.- built pier will resume in the coming days, the Israeli military said on Saturday, after repairs to the structure were completed.
articles.title: Gaza aid through U.S. pier will resume in coming days, Israel says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Danish police said on Saturday a 39-year-old man would appear in front of a judge for preliminary questioning in relation to an assault on the country's Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen in central Copenhagen late on Friday.
articles.title: Suspect to face preliminary questioning after assault on Danish PM Frederiksen

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli forces rescued four hostages alive from two separate locations in the central Gaza area of al-Nuseirat on Saturday, the military said.
articles.title: Israeli forces rescue four live hostages from Gaza, military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Suspected Islamist rebels killed at least 10 people in an overnight attack on a village in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, a local official and a civil society leader said on Saturday.
articles.title: Suspected Islamists kill at least 10 in attack on eastern Congo village

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Kate, Britain's Princess of Wales who is undergoing preventative chemotherapy for cancer, has written to an army regiment to apologise for missing a military parade on Saturday, adding that she hoped to be back very soon.
articles.title: Britain's Kate apologises for missing parade, hopes to be back 'very soon'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Rescuers continued searching for British TV presenter Michael Mosley on the mountainous Greek island of Symi on Saturday, the third day of a wide operation launched after he was reported missing by his wife.
articles.title: Rescuers search for British TV doctor for a third day on Greek island

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Malaysian authorities defended their decision to evict hundreds of sea nomads from their homes off the coast of Sabah state this week, saying it was aimed at boosting security and combating cross-border crime.
articles.title: Malaysia defends eviction of sea nomads, citing security concerns

articles.author: Barbara Erling, Kuba Stezycki, Kacper Pempel
articles.description: Surrounded by lush forests, a dozen people huddled near a razor-tipped fence along the Belarus border, waiting for a chance to scale it or push aside its slats to head west into Poland.
articles.title: Tensions flare on Poland-Belarus border as more migrants arrive
